This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring Memorial Day, May 28, 2012, as a day of prayer for permanent peace. The proclamation honors the men and women in uniform who have sacrificed their lives in service to their country. It acknowledges the historical significance of fallen service members and emphasizes the importance of their legacy in ensuring the security, prosperity, and freedom of the nation. The proclamation also requests that the flag be flown at half-staff until noon on Memorial Day and encourages individuals to observe a National Moment of Remembrance at 3:00 p.m. local time.